simplenlg.features

Enum Gender

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Gender>
      • simplenlg.features.Gender
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Gender>

    public enum Gender
extends java.lang.Enum<Gender>

    An enumeration representing the gender of the subject of a noun phrase, or the object or subject of a verb phrase. It is most commonly used with personal pronouns. The gender is recorded in the Feature.GENDER feature and applies to nouns and pronouns.

    Version:
    4.0
    Author:
    A. Gatt and D. Westwater, University of Aberdeen.
